race.description: Geraldton Toyota Family Day Sunday 16th Nov Hcp (C1)
race.comment: QUICK AS SILVER (1) was a comfortable Maiden winner and then held that number placing at York. Peaks today and keeps the handy 3kg claim. He can bounce back in this lineup. LEONARDO DA GREY (2) showed early speed from an outside draw and held a forward position before fading beaten 4L lengths. He's switched to a local stable and drops back to a short sprint on a 50-day return. Has the low barrier and the ability and will finish hard. YALLINGUP GIRL (4) resumes and has switched from the Parnham stable. She's been racing in stronger at Bunbury and has placed 2/4 fresh. May find it a touch short but like the above is hard to risk in this company. WEAPONIZE (7) surprised the market placing over this trip last time after settling last. Draws the inside barrier again but will be around the mark holding the form.
